<item>
            <title>[KARAF-2] When installing features, we need to osgi/refresh some bundles to allow optional imports to be resolved</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KARAF-2</link>
                <project id="12311140" key="KARAF">Karaf</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For example, before the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SMX4-222&quot; title=&quot;Jsp support is not enabled. Is org.ops4j.pax.web.jsp bundle installed?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SMX4-222&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SMX4-222&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the jsp bundle was installed after the core web service, thus making jsp not working.&lt;br/&gt;
When installing the jsp bundle, we should refresh the core web server, or maybe adding the core web service bundle to the web feature in addition to the web-core, and make the refresh when an already installed bundle is required by a feature (i think it would make more sense and be easier).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
